title: Supercars 2017: Will Davison new livery, Woodstock Bourbon sponsor Tekno Autosports, pics, photos | Geelong Advertiser
text:
Supercars: Will Davison reveals Woodstock Bourbon livery for several 2017 races Staff writers, FOX SPORTS February 2, 2017 5:04pm 
WILL Davison will look to defend his Bathurst 1000 victory in 2017 with new colours on his Tekno Autosports Holden, Woodstock Bourbon backing the No. 19 at the big events on the Supercars calendar. 
The Woodstock colours will adorn the Tekno Holden at the Clipsal 500 Adelaide, Townsville 400, Sandown 500, Bathurst 1000 and Gold Coast 600. 
The brand has increased its involvement with the Supercars championship in recent years, acting as title sponsor of last year’s Winton SuperSprint, but this is the first time it has moved to become a primary sponsor on a car. 
“In our past two years’ involvement with Supercars we have seen unbelievable passion from both the teams and fans of the sport. 
“Seeing a tight-knit and passionate team like Tekno come through the Supercars championship, and to rise up and win the Bathurst 1000, really showed us that they are a team we would love to align with Woodstock. 
“We are really excited to continue our involvement in the Supercars through our sponsorship of Tekno Woodstock Racing.” 
No word yet on what the remainder of Tekno’s sponsorship structure will look like for the 2017 season. media_camera Davison’s new-look Woodstock Commodore. media_camera Davison and his new-look Woodstock Commodore. media_camera
